      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Apex Pro 5 boasts a 6.7-inch OLED display with 120Hz refresh and 5G connectivity, while the Zenith X features a 6.8-inch LCD screen running at 90Hz and is limited to 4G networks. In terms of power, the Apex Pro 5 includes a massive 5000mAh battery paired with fast 25W charging, whereas the Zenith X relies on a smaller 4500mAh unit that only supports 15W charging speeds. Camera performance is split between the Apex Pro 5's 50MP main sensor and the Zenith X's higher 64MP main camera, though the latter sacrifices its ultrawide lens to a lower 10MP resolution compared to the Apex's 12MP option. Durability also differs significantly, with the Apex Pro 5 achieving IP68 water and dust resistance against the Zenith X's slightly lower IP67 rating. Ultimately, the Apex Pro 5 wins on connectivity, battery life, and display quality, while the Zenith X offers a marginally larger screen and higher megapixel count for main photography.",
